\pard\sa80\sb160{\cf3\b\fs24 HOW IT WORKS}\par
\pard\fi-200\li200\sa70\fs20 {\cf2\b\'95}\tab Each of your six teams scores on its own; add them up for your running total.\par
\pard\fi-200\li200\sa70\fs20 {\cf2\b\'95}\tab Group placement bonuses are awarded once each group concludes.\par
\pard\fi-200\li200\sa70\fs20 {\cf2\b\'95}\tab Knockout matches decided on penalties count as a win for the side that advances.\par
\pard\fi-200\li200\sa70\fs20 {\cf2\b\'95}\tab The "all teams advance" bonus (+3) needs all six of your teams to reach the Round of 32.\par
\pard\sa80\sb160{\cf3\b\fs24 STANDINGS, TIEBREAKERS & DAILY BRIEFING}\par
\pard\sa180\fs20 Standings are ranked by total points. Ties are broken at the commissioner's discretion (suggested: whose teams reached the furthest stage); Nicky is commissioner. Every morning, all participants receive a recap of the previous day's results and points, the updated standings, and that day's fixtures with each team's owner \'97 plus a live tracker page kept current throughout the day.\par
